00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,000
 Verse 1.

169
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,000
 "The Lord is my shepherd.

170
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,000
 I shall not be in want."

171
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,000
 And so this is a familiar occupation of David.

172
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 If he owned a gym, he'd be like, "The Lord is my trainer."

173
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,000
 If he worked at a hospital, he'd be like, "The Lord is my doctor."

174
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 If he was a teacher, he'd be like, "The Lord is my professor."

175
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 Or a student, "The Lord is my teacher."

176
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:28,000
 But because he's a shepherd, he's like, "Hey, I know how I care for the sheep.

177
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,000
 I know the care that I give to these animals."

178
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:37,000
 So God, Yehovah, creator of the heavens and the earth, is my shepherd.

179
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
 He cares for me.

180
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,000
 He cares for me.

181
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 He looks after me.

182
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
