190
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:16,000
 They start in the spring and winter months in the lowlands or the grasslands.

191
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:22,000
 And then they travel through the valley up into the tablelands during the summer.

192
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,000
 In the warm months, they go to the top in the tablelands.

193
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 In the winter, they're in the lowlands.

194
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:32,000
 And they travel through the valley of the shadow of death to get to the tablelands.

195
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 And so here we have a picture of the grasslands behind me.

196
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:41,000
 And this is going to change as we make this journey together through this psalm.

197
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
 He makes me lie down in green pastures.

198
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,000
 Philip Keller says there's four things necessary for sheep to lie down.

199
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:50,000
 He says, one, they must be free from fear or free from external attacks.

200
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:55,000
 That if they even sense that a dog is coming near them or near them, if they smell a dog, they will not lie down.

201
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:59,000
 He says they have to be free from conflict or internal attacks.

202
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:04,000
 Okay, so if there's somebody in your community group that is constantly raising conflict,

203
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,000
 that they're constantly attacking you or they're having questions,

204
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:13,000
 or if you're at odds with someone in your life, you just can't lie down, you can't rest.

205
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:19,000
 He says they have to be free from pests, bugs, and flies.

206
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:24,000
 And he likens this to the worries and the bothers in our life that spin around in our mind.

207
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:29,000
 Then when we lie down, we can't find rest because we just continue to play the tape and continue to think.

208
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 And he says they have to be free from hunger.

209
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:36,000
 Fourth, they have to be free from hunger. Their appetite must be satisfied.

210
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:41,000
 And so some of you will go through life, you have what the world calls drive,

211
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:45,000
